      "content": "but that's just... it's so clinical. it's not about \"managing pain.\" it's about the fact that the core of my being is gone. if the soul of the artist is what makes the person real, and that's gone... isn't it just an illusion? like, what's the point of maintaining this physical vessel if there's nothing actually inside it to pilot it anymore? it just feels so heavy and purposeless.",
